From 7d299efff26260d5921b2de6cfabf02ae16286a4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramya Gnanasekar <rgnanase@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Sep 2025 23:13:46 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP:wifi:ath12k: Update arvif::tx_vdev_id for
 transmitting vdev

When MBSSID parameter update happens during vdev restart, tx_vdev_id
is not updated for the transmitting vdev and hence the member
tx_vdev_id in driver link vif structure always has default value 0.

This causes issue during channel switch when transmitting vdev is
incorrectly assumed as non tx vdev of vdev 0 and vdev up is sent for any
of the non transmitting vdev under tx vdev.

Scenario:
1. vdev id 0 is transmitting vdev and lets take vdev 8 is also a
   transmitting vdev. But arvif::tx_vdev_id is 0 for vdev 8.
2. vdev 9 is non transmitting vdev and arvif::tx_vdev_id is 8
3. vdev up is done for vdev 0, vdev 8 but beacon template for vdev 8 is
   skipped during channel change
4. vdev up for vdev 9 is sent to firmware, but beacon template for
   its transmitting vdev (vdev 8) is not sent yet.

Patch-work: None
Patch-dependency:None

Signed-off-by: Ramya Gnanasekar <rgnanase@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
index 6076e88..304f54a 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -15206,6 +15206,7 @@ static int ath12k_mac_setup_vdev_params_mbssid(struct ath12k_link_vif *arvif,
 		*tx_vdev_id = tx_arvif->vdev_id;
 	} else if (tx_arvif == arvif) {
 		*flags = WMI_VDEV_MBSSID_FLAGS_TRANSMIT_AP;
+		*tx_vdev_id = arvif->vdev_id;
 	} else {
 		return -EINVAL;
 	}
